MANUAL QA TESTING PORTFOLIO
Author: Mohammad Taha
Role: Aspiring Manual QA Engineer

------------------------------------------------------------

ABOUT THIS REPOSITORY

This repository contains my hands-on practice work in Manual Software Testing. 
It includes structured test cases created using MS Excel for different application modules 
by applying standard QA methodologies and test case design techniques.

The objective of this repository is to demonstrate:

- Understanding of SDLC and STLC
- Practical implementation of test case design techniques
- Ability to structure and document test scenarios
- Knowledge of validation and negative testing
- Organized QA documentation skills

------------------------------------------------------------

MODULES COVERED

1) Authentication Module (Login and Password Validation)

Scope:
- Login functionality testing
- Password validation rules testing
- Input field validation
- Negative testing scenarios

Techniques Used:
- Boundary Value Analysis (BVA)
- Equivalence Partitioning (EP)
- Positive Testing
- Negative Testing

Validations Covered:
- Uppercase character requirement
- Lowercase character requirement
- Numeric character requirement
- Minimum and maximum length validation
- Invalid input handling

------------------------------------------------------------

2) Form Validation Testing

Scope:
- Mandatory field validation
- Invalid input handling
- Edge case testing
- Field-level validation testing

Activities Performed:
- Designed structured test scenarios
- Assigned appropriate priority levels
- Prepared execution-ready test sheets
- Maintained Pass/Fail/Not Executed status tracking

------------------------------------------------------------

REPOSITORY CONTENTS

This repository includes:

- Manual test case Excel files
- Structured Test Case IDs
- Preconditions and Test Steps
- Test Data and Expected Results
- Execution status tracking
- Priority classification

------------------------------------------------------------

TOOLS USED

- MS Excel (Test Case Documentation)
- GitHub (Version Control and Portfolio Hosting)

------------------------------------------------------------

TESTING APPROACH FOLLOWED

1. Requirement understanding
2. Test scenario identification
3. Test case design
4. Application of BVA and EP techniques
5. Organizing structured test documentation
6. Preparing execution-ready test sheets

------------------------------------------------------------

OBJECTIVE

This repository reflects my continuous learning journey toward becoming a professional QA Engineer. 
I am actively improving my skills in manual testing and expanding toward automation testing in upcoming phases.

